Lagos State Water Regulatory Commission (LASWARCO) has shut down Viju Industries Nigeria Limited in Ikeja Industrial Estate over failure to obtain the permit to use a Water Treatment Plant According to the Director of Monitoring and Compliance Unit, Lanre Owoturo, in a statement over the weekend, the offence was among other undisclosed violations. “LASWARCO is a Lagos State Regulatory Agency empowered by Law to enforce compliance. Ukraine Accuses Russia Of ‘Planning Acts Of Genocide’ Constitution Amendment: NLC Vows To Shame Lawmakers Who Vote… “The Commission will not watch companies operate illegally without obtaining all necessary documents to operate for the safety of citizens”, Owoturo said.